New Records: Yordan Alvarez became the second Astros player in history to hit at least 30 homers in four consecutive seasons
Key Match Events: Yordan Alvarez hit his 29th and 30th homers of the season
Others: The Astros swept the four-game series and have won five in a row
The Astros (75-62) improved to a season-high 13 games over.500
The Astros now own the tiebreaker over the Royals by taking the season series over Kansas City, 4-3
